  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "MECHANICAL SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p><p>Supervise and coordinate all mechanical installation, maintenance, and repair works at Shipyard/workshop.</p></p><p><p>Plan daily work activities and allocate manpower efficiently to meet project schedules.</p></p><p><p>Ensure mechanical works are carried out as per approved drawings, specifications, and safety standards.</p></p><p><p>Monitor work progress and maintain quality control of mechanical activities.</p></p><p><p>Conduct inspection, testing, and commissioning of mechanical equipment and systems.</p></p><p><p>Coordinate with engineers, clients, subcontractors, and other trades to ensure smooth workflow.</p></p><p><p>Ensure proper use of tools, equipment, and materials to minimize wastage.</p></p><p><p>Enforce workplace safety rules and ensure compliance with HSE requirements.</p></p><p><p>Prepare daily progress reports, work completion reports, and material requests.</p></p><p><p>Attend toolbox meetings and site coordination meetings.</p></p><p><p>Identify technical issues and provide practical solutions on site.</p></p><p><p>Ensure preventive and corrective maintenance activities are carried out effectively.</p></p><p><p>Guide and train technicians and helpers to improve performance and workmanship.</p></p><p><p>Willing and able to work <strong>overtime, night shifts, weekends, and public holidays</strong> as per project requirements.</p></p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 15,
